<p>Theresa May has been asked to urgently clear up the &ldquo;shocking&rdquo; confusion over the Brexit process, after Boris Johnson today directly contradicted David Davis over whether the government had made contingency plans for leaving the EU without a deal.</p><br />
<p>Speaking in the Commons today, the foreign secretary said &ldquo;there is no plan for no deal because we are going to get a great deal.&rdquo;</p><br />
<p>However in March, the Brexit secretary sought to reassure voters that the government was prepared.</p><br />
<p>&ldquo;We have been planing for the contingencies, all the various outcomes, all the possible outcomes of the negotiation,&rdquo; he told the BBC&rsquo;s Andrew Marr Show.</p><br />
<p>Asked if this included a &ldquo;proper plan for no deal&rdquo;, Davis added: &ldquo;Oh yes, oh yes.&rdquo;</p><br />
<div class="embed-asset embed" data-type="embed-asset" data-provider="Embed" data-title=""><br />
<div class="embed-code"><!-- TAG START { player: "Huff Post UK News&Pols - WIDE Click to Play", for: "HuffPost UK (PUB) [Huffington Post UK]" } --><br />
<div id="vidible_14997819622" class="vdb_player vdb_56c60983e4b03a39c93c9fb256be00124076e70ee4171d93" vdb_params="m.embeded=cms_video_plugin_uk.edit.huffpost.net&amp;m.fwkeyvalues=sponsorship%3DSPONSORSHIP_NAME&amp;m.fwsitesection=composer" data-placeholder="//img.vidible.tv/prod/2017-07/11/5964d8c31de5a1538d1370eb/5964d8cb9e6fb34443f4702b_o_A_v2.jpg?w=1440&amp;h=900">	<script type="text/javascript" src="//delivery.vidible.tv/jsonp/pid=56c60983e4b03a39c93c9fb2/vid=5964d8c31de5a1538d1370eb/56be00124076e70ee4171d93.js?m.embeded=cms_video_plugin_uk.edit.huffpost.net"></script><script type='text/javascript'>function onPlayerReadyVidible(e){'undefined'!=typeof HPTrack&&HPTrack.Vid.Vidible_track(e)}!function(e,i){if(e.vdb_Player){if('object'==typeof commercial_video){var a='',o='m.fwsitesection='+commercial_video.site_and_category;if(a+=o,commercial_video['package']){var c='&m.fwkeyvalues=sponsorship%3D'+commercial_video['package'];a+=c}e.setAttribute('vdb_params',a)}i(e.vdb_Player)}else{var t=arguments.callee;setTimeout(function(){t(e,i)},0)}}(document.getElementById('vidible_2'),onPlayerReadyVidible);</script></div><br />
