    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:86:"http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2017/07/11/will-brexit-actually-happen_n_17454942.html";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:4:"true";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"Will Brexit Actually Happen? You&#039;d Goddam Better Hope So";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:6:"author";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"Chris York";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:124:"http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2017/07/11/will-brexit-actually-happen_n_17454942.html?utm_hp_ref=uk-politics&ir=UK+Politics";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 11 Jul 2017 09:49:08 -0400";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14714:"<p>With more and more people expressing doubt over whether or not <a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/news/brexit/">Brexit</a> will actually happen, now seems as good a time as any to remind ourselves just why it should definitely still go ahead.</p><br />
<h4>1)&nbsp;Because No One Wants To Holiday In Europe Anyway</h4><br />
<p>Wayne knows what&rsquo;s good for him - a solid weekend camping in the UK, none of this foreign holiday bollocks.</p><br />
<p>He made this point incredibly <a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/james-obrien-brexit-voter_uk_59638b97e4b0615b9e9319e7" target="_blank">clearly to James O&rsquo;Brien this week</a> and definitely didn&rsquo;t get totally put in his place and exposed for a complete understanding of how the EU works.</p><br />
<div class="embed-asset embed" data-type="embed-asset" data-provider="Embed" data-title=""><br />
<div class="embed-code"><!-- TAG START { player: "Huff Post UK News&Pols - Click to Play", for: "HuffPost UK (PUB) [Huffington Post UK]" } --><br />
<div id="vidible_14997809541" class="vdb_player vdb_56c6056ee4b01f2b7e1b5f3556be00124076e70ee4171d93" vdb_params="m.embeded=cms_video_plugin_uk.edit.huffpost.net&amp;m.fwkeyvalues=sponsorship%3DSPONSORSHIP_NAME&amp;m.fwsitesection=composer" data-placeholder="//img.vidible.tv/prod/2017-07/10/596351ebb90afb5c991b426f/596351ea670984788158108a_o_F_v0.jpg?w=1440&amp;h=900">	<script type="text/javascript" src="//delivery.vidible.tv/jsonp/pid=56c6056ee4b01f2b7e1b5f35/vid=596351ebb90afb5c991b426f/56be00124076e70ee4171d93.js?m.embeded=cms_video_plugin_uk.edit.huffpost.net"></script><script type='text/javascript'>function onPlayerReadyVidible(e){'undefined'!=typeof HPTrack&&HPTrack.Vid.Vidible_track(e)}!function(e,i){if(e.vdb_Player){if('object'==typeof commercial_video){var a='',o='m.fwsitesection='+commercial_video.site_and_category;if(a+=o,commercial_video['package']){var c='&m.fwkeyvalues=sponsorship%3D'+commercial_video['package'];a+=c}e.setAttribute('vdb_params',a)}i(e.vdb_Player)}else{var t=arguments.callee;setTimeout(function(){t(e,i)},0)}}(document.getElementById('vidible_1'),onPlayerReadyVidible);</script></div><br />
<!-- TAG END { date: 7/11/17 } --></div></div><br />
     <br />
<p>The best bit? When Wayne eloquently explained what we would do if Brits needed a visa to visit the Continent after Brexit.</p><br />
<blockquote class="pull-quote"><br />
<span class="quote">I don’t know. I don’t really want to go to France.</span><br />
<span class="attribution">Wayne, Brexit Legend</span><br />
</blockquote><br />
     <br />
<p>Too right Wayne! James O&rsquo;Brien is peak-Remoaner.</p><br />
<div class="embed-asset embed" data-type="embed-asset" data-provider="Embed" data-title=""><br />
<div class="embed-code"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" align="center"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">Surely someone will come up with one even remotely sensible reason for Brexit, eventually? Won&#39;t be coming from Wayne though <a href="https://twitter.com/mrjamesob">@mrjamesob</a> <a href="https://t.co/vJ5TiVImn7">https://t.co/vJ5TiVImn7</a></p>&mdash; Gary Lineker (@GaryLineker) <a href="https://twitter.com/GaryLineker/status/884689751118360576">July 11, 2017</a></blockquote><br />
<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div></div><br />
     <br />
<p>And what would you know, Lineker?&nbsp;Stick to football.</p><br />
<p>&nbsp;</p><br />
<h4>2) Because Feelings Are More Important Than Food</h4><br />
<p>O&rsquo;Brien again here, with the cheek to suggest that eating is important.</p><br />
<p>A brave Brexiteer who <a href="http://www.lbc.co.uk/radio/presenters/james-obrien/i-dont-care-if-we-starve-at-least-well-be-free-eu/" target="_blank">sent an anonymous text r</a>esponding to all O&rsquo;Brien&rsquo;s fancy &ldquo;facts&rdquo; and &ldquo;logic&rdquo; really hit the nail on the head.</p><br />
<div class="embed-asset embed" data-type="embed-asset" data-provider="Embed" data-title=""><br />
<div class="embed-code"><!-- TAG START { player: "Huff Post UK News&Pols - Click to Play", for: "HuffPost UK (PUB) [Huffington Post UK]" } --><br />
<div id="vidible_14997809542" class="vdb_player vdb_56c6056ee4b01f2b7e1b5f3556be00124076e70ee4171d93" vdb_params="m.embeded=cms_video_plugin_uk.edit.huffpost.net&amp;m.fwkeyvalues=sponsorship%3DSPONSORSHIP_NAME&amp;m.fwsitesection=composer" data-placeholder="//img.vidible.tv/prod/2017-07/10/59637f0b92fdde6bcab54f62/59637f0bc5ab0e586dba6276_o_F_v0.jpg?w=1440&amp;h=900">	<script type="text/javascript" src="//delivery.vidible.tv/jsonp/pid=56c6056ee4b01f2b7e1b5f35/vid=59637f0b92fdde6bcab54f62/56be00124076e70ee4171d93.js?m.embeded=cms_video_plugin_uk.edit.huffpost.net"></script><script type='text/javascript'>function onPlayerReadyVidible(e){'undefined'!=typeof HPTrack&&HPTrack.Vid.Vidible_track(e)}!function(e,i){if(e.vdb_Player){if('object'==typeof commercial_video){var a='',o='m.fwsitesection='+commercial_video.site_and_category;if(a+=o,commercial_video['package']){var c='&m.fwkeyvalues=sponsorship%3D'+commercial_video['package'];a+=c}e.setAttribute('vdb_params',a)}i(e.vdb_Player)}else{var t=arguments.callee;setTimeout(function(){t(e,i)},0)}}(document.getElementById('vidible_2'),onPlayerReadyVidible);</script></div><br />
<!-- TAG END { date: 7/11/17 } --></div></div><br />
     <br />
<p>The Brexiteer wrote:</p><br />
<blockquote><br />
<p>&ldquo;Hi James, people wanted to feel English. It&rsquo;s a feeling. People don&rsquo;t care if we go down starving, at least we&rsquo;ll be free.&nbsp;Free from being told what to do by [the] EU.&rdquo;</p><br />
</blockquote><br />
<p>Good job too because we might not have the strength to fight back...but at least we&rsquo;ll be free.</p><br />
<div class="embed-asset embed" data-type="embed-asset" data-provider="Embed" data-title=""><br />
<div class="embed-code"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" align="center"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">Anyone else noticed how Brextremists have stopped saying Brexit will be good for Britain, just that it has to happen cos of 23/6/16 vote?</p>&mdash; Alastair Campbell (@campbellclaret) <a href="https://twitter.com/campbellclaret/status/884692615928655872">July 11, 2017</a></blockquote><br />
<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div></div><br />
     <br />
<p>Shut up Campbell.&nbsp;</p><br />
<p>&nbsp;</p><br />
<h4>3) Older Leave Voters &lsquo;Have More Life Experience&rsquo; So They Can&rsquo;t Be Wrong</h4><br />
<p>This gent was responding to a completely unreasonable Remoaner who dared to say &ldquo;the Leave guys didn&rsquo;t actually know what they were campaigning for so those of us voting also didn&rsquo;t know what was going to happen&rdquo;.</p><br />
<p>He hit back:</p><br />
<blockquote><br />
<p>&ldquo;I&rsquo;m working, I&rsquo;m a taxpayer. I could say &lsquo;I&rsquo;m older than you, I&rsquo;m wiser than you, life experience&rsquo;, so my vote is worth more, it&rsquo;s more valuable in that aspect. It&rsquo;s not fair, but it&rsquo;s a comeback.&rdquo;</p><br />
</blockquote><br />
<div class="embed-asset embed" data-type="embed-asset" data-provider="Embed" data-title=""><br />
<div class="embed-code"><!-- TAG START { player: "Huff Post UK News&Pols - Click to Play", for: "HuffPost UK (PUB) [Huffington Post UK]" } --><br />
<div id="vidible_14997809543" class="vdb_player vdb_56c6056ee4b01f2b7e1b5f3556be00124076e70ee4171d93" vdb_params="m.embeded=cms_video_plugin_uk.edit.huffpost.net&amp;m.fwkeyvalues=sponsorship%3DSPONSORSHIP_NAME&amp;m.fwsitesection=composer" data-placeholder="//img.vidible.tv/prod/2017-07/07/595f399183b51f315a269bd2/595f39a09e6fb34443f44d0c_o_A_v2.jpg?w=1440&amp;h=900">	<script type="text/javascript" src="//delivery.vidible.tv/jsonp/pid=56c6056ee4b01f2b7e1b5f35/vid=595f399183b51f315a269bd2/56be00124076e70ee4171d93.js?m.embeded=cms_video_plugin_uk.edit.huffpost.net"></script><script type='text/javascript'>function onPlayerReadyVidible(e){'undefined'!=typeof HPTrack&&HPTrack.Vid.Vidible_track(e)}!function(e,i){if(e.vdb_Player){if('object'==typeof commercial_video){var a='',o='m.fwsitesection='+commercial_video.site_and_category;if(a+=o,commercial_video['package']){var c='&m.fwkeyvalues=sponsorship%3D'+commercial_video['package'];a+=c}e.setAttribute('vdb_params',a)}i(e.vdb_Player)}else{var t=arguments.callee;setTimeout(function(){t(e,i)},0)}}(document.getElementById('vidible_3'),onPlayerReadyVidible);</script></div><br />
<!-- TAG END { date: 7/11/17 } --></div></div><br />
     <br />
<p>Then she said something about how being older doesn&rsquo;t necessarily mean being wiser, but that&rsquo;s not important.&nbsp;</p><br />
<h4>4) &nbsp;Because Knowing About Brexit Negotiations Isn&rsquo;t Important, Only That We Brexit&nbsp;</h4><br />
<p>Wendy has her head screwed on right. She made the brilliant point last month that the British public don&rsquo;t need to know anything about Brexit negotiations until it&rsquo;s actually happened.</p><br />
<p>She got justifiably irate when that wretched Brexit saboteur, Gina Miller, dared to suggest the public in a democratic country might like to know the terms on which the biggest political decision in generations is being conducted.</p><br />
<div class="embed-asset embed" data-type="embed-asset" data-provider="Embed" data-title=""><br />
<div class="embed-code"><!-- TAG START { player: "Huff Post UK News&Pols - Click to Play", for: "HuffPost UK (PUB) [Huffington Post UK]" } --><br />
<div id="vidible_14997809544" class="vdb_player vdb_56c6056ee4b01f2b7e1b5f3556be00124076e70ee4171d93" vdb_params="m.embeded=cms_video_plugin_uk.edit.huffpost.net&amp;m.fwkeyvalues=sponsorship%3DSPONSORSHIP_NAME&amp;m.fwsitesection=composer" data-placeholder="//img.vidible.tv/prod/2017-06/23/594cc8dff3bdc97f88871fd4/594cc8e59e6fb34443f3a0cc_o_A_v2.jpg?w=1440&amp;h=900">	<script type="text/javascript" src="//delivery.vidible.tv/jsonp/pid=56c6056ee4b01f2b7e1b5f35/vid=594cc8dff3bdc97f88871fd4/56be00124076e70ee4171d93.js?m.embeded=cms_video_plugin_uk.edit.huffpost.net"></script><script type='text/javascript'>function onPlayerReadyVidible(e){'undefined'!=typeof HPTrack&&HPTrack.Vid.Vidible_track(e)}!function(e,i){if(e.vdb_Player){if('object'==typeof commercial_video){var a='',o='m.fwsitesection='+commercial_video.site_and_category;if(a+=o,commercial_video['package']){var c='&m.fwkeyvalues=sponsorship%3D'+commercial_video['package'];a+=c}e.setAttribute('vdb_params',a)}i(e.vdb_Player)}else{var t=arguments.callee;setTimeout(function(){t(e,i)},0)}}(document.getElementById('vidible_4'),onPlayerReadyVidible);</script></div><br />
<!-- TAG END { date: 7/11/17 } --></div></div><br />
     <br />
<p>Taking no crap whatsoever, she said:</p><br />
<blockquote><br />
<p>&ldquo;You don&rsquo;t need to know. None of us needs to know, yet, exactly what&rsquo;s on the table.</p><br />
</blockquote><br />
<div class="content-list-component text"><br />
<p>Another audience member then told Wendy she should &ldquo;want to know what&rsquo;s going on&rdquo;, before being silenced by her stern reply.&nbsp;</p><br />
<p>&ldquo;No, because we know we want to get out of it and that&rsquo;s the most important thing.&rdquo;</p><br />
<p>Damn straight Wendy.</p><br />
</div><br />
<div class="embed-asset embed" data-type="embed-asset" data-provider="Embed" data-title=""><br />
<div class="embed-code"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" align="center"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">&quot;None of us need to know” what Theresa May wants to get out of Brexit, apparently.<br><br>I think that’s called “taking back control&quot;<a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/bbcqt?src=hash">#bbcqt</a></p>&mdash; Mikey Smith (@mikeysmith) <a href="https://twitter.com/mikeysmith/status/878011868513574912">June 22, 2017</a></blockquote><br />
<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div></div><br />
     <br />
<p>Whatever Mikey, the Mirror is practically Communist.</p><br />
<p>&nbsp;</p><br />
<h4>5) Because Nigel Knows More About Nuclear Than So-Called &lsquo;Experts&rsquo;</h4><br />
<p>Nuclear Nige, amiright?</p><br />
<div class="embed-asset embed" data-type="embed-asset" data-provider="Embed" data-title=""><br />
<div class="embed-code"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" align="center"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">The liberal media are bringing Project Fear back. I am sick to death of the blatant anti-Brexit bias carried out by the BBC. <a href="https://t.co/aqqB7WP9Xh">pic.twitter.com/aqqB7WP9Xh</a></p>&mdash; Nigel Farage (@Nigel_Farage) <a href="https://twitter.com/Nigel_Farage/status/884514872226177026">July 10, 2017</a></blockquote><br />
<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div></div><br />
     <br />
<p>The one and only Farge, who has never been elected an MP only because he&rsquo;s not a member of the corrupt liberal elite like those bloody City bankers, is angry.</p><br />
<p>Really angry.</p><br />
<p>Farage reckons George Osborne is scaring people silly about maintaining access to vital nuclear materials, but says it&rsquo;ll all be OK because we can get them from all over the world.</p><br />
<p>Five&nbsp;&ldquo;nuclear scientists&rdquo; said the <a href="https://www.buzzfeed.com/tomchivers/these-scientists-say-brexit-is-a-mess-for-british-nuclear?utm_term=.hdwRqo4GA#.vqrPZejxX" target="_blank">whole industry would be a mess after Brexit</a>, but what do they know? Nuclear is only a theory anyway, there&rsquo;s no evidence it exists.&nbsp;</p><br />
<div class="embed-asset embed" data-type="embed-asset" data-provider="Embed" data-title=""><br />
<div class="embed-code"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" align="center" data-conversation="none"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">BBC sensible to make clear the severe negative economic consequences of the Brexxit decision and to expose the untruths your brexidiots told</p>&mdash; Danny Blanchflower (@D_Blanchflower) <a href="https://twitter.com/D_Blanchflower/status/884541434904403968">July 10, 2017</a></blockquote><br />
<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div></div><br />
     <br />
<p>Oh sod off Blanchflower. What kind of sissy name is that anyway?</p><br />
