    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:88:"http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2017/07/10/is-theresa-may-labour-bizarre_n_17453774.html";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:4:"true";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:89:"Is Theresa May Labour? And More Bizarre Most Googled Questions About Tory Cabinet Members";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:6:"author";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Becky Barnes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:126:"http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2017/07/10/is-theresa-may-labour-bizarre_n_17453774.html?utm_hp_ref=uk-politics&ir=UK+Politics";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 11 Jul 2017 05:21:43 -0400";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6512:"<p>No, Theresa May is not Labour. That&rsquo;s the answer to one of the most Googled question about the Prime Minister right now.</p><br />
<p>Another disturbing question showing up in the top results is: &ldquo;Is Theresa May dead?&rdquo;</p><br />
<p>Maybe it was former chief whip Andrew Mitchell&rsquo;s recent comments that the Prime Minister is &ldquo;dead in the water&rdquo; that got lost in translation.</p><br />
<br />
<p>Anyway, panic not, we can thankfully confirm May is well and truly alive. Here she is welcoming Australian Prime Minister Malcolm Turnbull to 10 Downing Street.</p><br />
<br />
<p>Worryingly, people really don&rsquo;t seem to be sure what political party May belongs to - with the third most Googled question right now being: &ldquo;Is Theresa May Conservative?&rdquo;</p><br />
<p>It could be her asking Labour leader Jeremy Corbyn and other rivals <a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/theresa-may-ideas-brexit-first-anniversary_uk_5962994be4b0d5b458eb5d74?utm_hp_ref=uk">for their help to deliver Brexit</a> in her first anniversary speech that got people confused.</p><br />
<p>Hopefully people were aware of what political party May was in if they voted for her in the recent general election.</p><br />
<p>If you&rsquo;re unsure, we can <em>exclusively</em> reveal that Theresa May is the leader of the <strong>Conservative</strong> party. Yes, we are being facetious.</p><br />
<br />
<p>People are also apparently interested in whether the PM is left-handed. As pictures of her signing important documents such as the Article 50 letter in the photo above suggest, she is right-handed.</p><br />
<p>We decided to find out more batsh*t crazy most Googled questions about the whole Tory cabinet - and bring you the answers, of course.</p><br />
<h3>Is Philip Hammond related to Richard Hammond?</h3><br />
<br />
<p>Despite having the same surname, we can confirm that Chancellor Philip and the former Top Gear, now The Grand Tour TV presenter Richard are not related. It seems they share a love of baby blue polka dot material though.</p><br />
<br />
<h3>Is Boris Johnson related to the Queen?</h3><br />
<br />
<p>As bizarre as it sounds, there is good reason for this crazy-sounding question.</p><br />
<p>When the now-Foreign Secretary went on the BBC One program Who Do You Think You Are? to trace his family tree in 2008, his paternal grandmother was revealed to be a descendant of a German prince. This prince - Paul Von Wurttemberg happened to be a descendant of King George II, which means BoJo is the great-great-great-great-great-great-great-great-grandson of the 18th century monarch. And thus is actually related to HRH.</p><br />
<p>Also, Johnson&rsquo;s grandad was half-Turkish so the first most Googled question &ldquo;Is Boris Johnson Turkish?&rdquo; isn&rsquo;t too ludicrous either.</p><br />
<br />
<h3>How tall is Justine Greening?</h3><br />
<br />
<p>We have to admit, we don&rsquo;t have the answer to this one about the Education Secretary at the moment. However, we&rsquo;ll bring you the answer to this important question as soon as we can.</p><br />
<div class="embed-asset embed" data-type="embed-asset" data-provider="Embed" data-title=""><br />
<div class="embed-code"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" align="center"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"><a href="https://twitter.com/JustineGreening">@JustineGreening</a> Hi Justine, Really bizarre question - but I wondered how tall you are? - doing a piece on most unusual Googled qs on MPs</p>&mdash; Becky Barnes (@BeckyBarnesB) <a href="https://twitter.com/BeckyBarnesB/status/884410369929875456">July 10, 2017</a></blockquote><br />
<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div></div><br />
     <br />
<br />
<h3>Is Michael Gove standing as an MP?</h3><br />
<br />
<p>Poor Michael Gove. Looks like no-one&rsquo;s been Googling anything new since before the general election on Thursday 8 June.</p><br />
<p>Anyway, Gove <em>did&nbsp;</em>stand this year, keeping the Surrey Heath seat he has held since 2005 for another term. He was also promoted to Environment Secretary in the subsequent Cabinet reshuffle.</p><br />
<br />
<h3>Is Jeremy Corbyn vegan?</h3><br />
<br />
<p>Aside from the Tory Cabinet, there are some pretty funny questions being asked about Jeremy Corbyn and the Labour shadow cabinet.</p><br />
<p>We&rsquo;ll get back to you very soon with the most bizarre questions asked about them.</p><br />
<p>But for now, we can reveal Jezza is a vegetarian, not a vegan.</p><br />
<br />
<p>Until then...</p><br />
